    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "ABOUT POLYMARKET\n\nPolymarket is the world’s largest prediction market platform. We enable individuals to express views on real-world events by trading on outcomes across politics, economics, sports, culture, and current affairs. Built as a peer-to-peer marketplace with no centralized “house,” Polymarket aggregates diverse opinions into transparent, market-based probabilities that reflect collective expectations about the future.\n\nWe're growing fast – both in terms of volume ($21B traded in 2025) and adoption as an alternative news source. Our ambition is to become a ubiquitous beacon of truth in global media and we need your help adding fuel to the fire.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nPolymarket is looking for a Developer Relations Manager who thrives at the intersection of technology, community, and business development. You'll be the bridge connecting our vibrant ecosystem of traders, builders, and partners with our core product team — driving growth through authentic relationships and technical excellence.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Community Leadership: Cultivate and champion our global network of developers, traders, and market creators. Turn community feedback into actionable product insights and ensure our builders feel supported and heard.\n\n - Technical Partnership Strategy: Guide external teams through integrations with Polymarket's APIs. You'll be the technical point person ensuring partners ship successful integrations while identifying opportunities to improve our developer experience.\n\n - Strategic Alliance Building: Source and nurture partnerships with crypto protocols, research institutions, media partners, and complementary platforms that expand Polymarket's reach and utility.\n\n - Ecosystem Development: Build deeper relationships with market creators, liquidity providers, and institutional participants who drive trading volume and market quality.\n\n - Grants Program Leadership: Run our ecosystem grants program end-to-end — from sourcing promising applications to shepherding funded projects through successful launches.\n\n - Internal Advocacy: Serve as the voice of our external community within Polymarket, working cross-functionally to ensure partner and developer needs shape our product roadmap.\n\n\nWHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - 3–5+ years in developer relations, business development, or ecosystem growth within crypto, DeFi, or emerging tech environments\n\n - Deep web3 fluency — you understand blockchain mechanics, smart contracts, and decentralized systems beyond surface level\n\n - API-first mindset — comfortable working with REST/GraphQL APIs, troubleshooting integrations, and guiding partners through technical implementations\n\n - Hands-on technical skills in Python or TypeScript for testing, debugging, and building proof-of-concepts\n\n - Exceptional communication — can translate complex technical concepts for diverse audiences, from developers to executives\n\n - Polymarket familiarity — knowledge of our existing APIs and platform, or demonstrated ability to rapidly learn new technical systems\n\n - Bonus points: Background in prediction markets, trading platforms, or quantitative finance\n\n\n\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Competitive salary \u0026 equity\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Full Health, Vision, \u0026 Dental coverage\n\n - 401k match\n\n - Hardware setup — new MacBook Pro, big display, \u0026 accessories",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
